  "elapsed_s": 10.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And, yet, you didn't trust yourself even to think in terms of freedom yet, because as long as you knew that you are under-- in-- in a Russian train in Russian territory, and you are being watched- and you are being watched undoubtedly-- then it had to be only between your mind and your soul, so to speak, that those realizations could be-- could have a sort of a dialogue, not even with next door person.",
      "word_count": 76
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "You suspected or assume that other person is sharing the same sort of emotion, the same sort of realizations as yourself.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But that is an assumption.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we did not dare-- when we arrived, finally, in Vladivostok, and we have transferred from the train on to that boat, we had a Russian military officer from the Coast Guard accompanying us on the boat right through the territorial waters of Russia.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That's right, of course, of course.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 6 SECONDS] And it was not so simple.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I had an experience in-- at the time of going through my luggage with papers, where I had a copy of my birth certificate saying that I am from Bialystock, whilst, in fact, I gave my original story as being a shoemaker's son from Warsaw, because I didn't want to give too much of my identity.",
      "word_count": 56
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And the man who looked at my papers, [INAUDIBLE] paper.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And when I saw him opening this piece of paper, it shows an extract, post-war, had it with the hammer and sickle.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I didn't have the original.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We had to ask for one.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And we got an extract from the new government [INAUDIBLE] the Russian government [INAUDIBLE] Bialystock.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "If he would have opened that piece of paper one more opening, I would have been finished.",
      "word_count": 17
    }
  ],
